<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Background Image Example</title>
    <style>
        /* General body styling */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            height: 100vh; /* Full height for the background image */
            background-image: url('https://via.placeholder.com/150'); /* Replace with your image URL */
            background-repeat: repeat; /* Repeat the background image */
            background-size: auto; /* Default size */
        }

        /* Container for content */
        .content {
            background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8); /* Semi-transparent background for readability */
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 50px auto; /* Center the content */
            text-align: center;
        }

        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }

        p {
            color: #666;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="content">
        <h1>Welcome to My Web Page</h1>
        <p>This page demonstrates how to use a background image with CSS.</p>
        <p>The background image repeats to fill the entire page.</p>
    </div>

</body>
